It can be configured in line 93, but I would like to use one variable to store the current configure and use that variable to compare instead of use the configure in effecterInfo.
I want to avoid to many code like:
 if (effecterInfo.effecterPdrType == PLDM_STATE_EFFECTER_PDR)

As the original design of `dbus_to_host_effecter`, the code is only applied for host. But I don't see any reason to limit the code for only host. The host effecter and other PLDM terminus effecter are the same.

I think we can change the file name to `dbus_to_terminus_effecter` or something like that.

@ManojKiran Eda, Can you give give your comment on this idea?
